title: Part E
stimulusHtml: Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.
descriptions: The response does not state that the demand for money and the nominal interest rate will increase and/or does not explain that the increase in the GDP deflator from Year 1 to Year 2 in Zuma indicates an increase in the price level, which will increase the demand for money and therefore increase the nominal interest rate.

The response states that the demand for money and the nominal interest rate will increase and explains that the increase in the GDP deflator from Year 1 to Year 2 in Zuma indicates an increase in the price level, which will increase the demand for money and therefore increase the nominal interest rate.
